item.title: One Direction 'Our Moment' Fragrance Racks Up $100-Million in Pre-Orders
item.description: One Direction has a hit fragrance to add to their hit movie, 'This Is Us,' and songs, like 'Best Song Ever.' As John Basedow (@JohnBasedow) reports, 'Our Moment,' the boys' debut perfume, has racked up $100-million in advance sales. The commercial, which features Harry, Zayn, Niall, Liam and Louis playing around with everything from flowers to feet, is targeted to the 'X Factor' boy band's large tween fan base.

item.title: 'Breaking Bad' Breaks Guinness World Record
item.description: AMC's popular series 'Breaking Bad' is among the few shows and celebrities making the cut in the 2014 Guinness Book of World Records. The drama debuted in 2008. Now in its fifth and final season, the show earned a record as the Highest Rated TV Series thanks to a score of 99 out of 100 on metacritic.com. Betty White, Justin Bieber and Taylor Swift were also featured celebs to score a record in the book. Krystin Goodwin has the story.

item.title: Girl Tweets YOLO After Blowing .341 BAC
item.description: A girl charged with running on the field during the Northern Illinois - Iowa football game blew a .341 BAC. That's like in the coma and death range levels of ethanol in her blood. Her tweets show that she was able to shrug the whole incident off. Patrick Jones (@Patrick_E_Jones) reports.

item.title: Jay Z Releases 'Holy Grail' Music Video on Facebook
item.description: Hip hop fans get ready. Jay Z's Facebook page holds the key to the 'Holy Grail' music video. The hit new single from Jaz Z's album 'Magna Carta... Holy Grail' features Justin Timberlake and premiered only on the rapper's Facebook page, making him the first artist to post a music video exclusively to the social media platform. In less than a few hours, the video had over 34,000 likes and over 24,000 shares. Krystin Goodwin has the story.

item.title: Kim Kardashian, Kanye Battle Over First Photos of North West: Report
item.description: Kim Kardashian and Kanye West are reportedly in a battle over where the first photos of their daughter, North West, should appear. As John Basedow (@JohnBasedow) reports, the 'Keeping Up With The Kardashians' star wants the cover of 'Vogue' while Yeezus favors social media. According to RadarOnline, Vogue Editor Anna Wintour may prefer that option, since she reportedly isn't too keen on the shots gracing her fashion magazine.
